				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Ok. In my ever so humble opinion this expansion easily tops em almost back to luclin. Let's review. I'm a pre-elemental mage in a pre-elemental guild on povar. During the week or so I've had the expansion (I live in podunk, north dakota. and it took me that long to break down and order it off the net) I've gotten 6 nearly elemental level equipment upgrades, and all of my 66 spells. I can solo again. It isn't easy, but it's doable and for the first time in ages, it's actually decent exp and equip. Tonight with CoW I trioed the Kyv Assassin in WoS with a druid, enchanter and my pet tanking. This was the famed 4 named spawn camp and if I'd been so inclined, the three of us could have held it.
<br />

<br />
Yes WoS is packed to all hell during any sort of normal playtime hours. But then do ya remember LOIO back in the day? Same deal. Forget who, but someone drew the comparison between OoW and Kunark. I'd say that was pretty accurate. I frequently get nostalgic in WoS for Overthere and such. Wasn't fun at the time, but it was there I really learned how to group.
<br />

<br />
What this expansion does that not a lot of others have is level the playing field. I am a casual gamer. I frequently take month long breaks from eq for real life stuff. I only have 130 or so AA and I've been playing since the summer of 2001. I just got done taking a month long break. In under a week I'm caught up. I get groups every night in WoS. If I can't get em by reputation (which is pretty good), I make them. Let's draw a comparison. My personal favorite pre OoW exp spot being that I'm pre elemental and un GoD flagged. 
<br />

<br />
Bastion of Thunder. AA% per kill: 2 or three in a full group. Chance at upgrades/loot: slim to none.
<br />

<br />
Walls of Slaughter: Real exp per kill: about 1/4 to 1/2 of a percent depending on the camp. AA% per kill: 1 to 2 in a full group with only 20% going to aa. Chance at upgrades/loot: MASSIVE. Nearly every single exp camp there has at least two or more named spawns. Throw a rock, you'll hit a named.
<br />

<br />
That Assassin I mentioned earlier was a red con at 67. My pet made a better thank than the group's 8khp SK. In Nobel's Causeway I can solo for exp and again, a chance at elementalish loot. That's from non named btw. I nuke as well as our guild's top wizzy atm. Granted, he doesn't have all his spells/aa yet, but neither do I.
<br />

<br />
I have yet to pass a night in this expansion without getting a rune. Had it a week have 7 runes. 6 of which I traded for minor and finished my 66 spells, one of which is a greater rune for the 69 spells. Now, it took me a HELL of a lot longer to get my PoP spells. I'm still don't have a single GoD spell. At the rate I'm going, 3 or 4 weeks should have me with the full set up to 68.
<br />

<br />
I haven't had this kind of class advantage since lvl 40 pre luclin, when I could solo group content. I can do that again. That in itself is enough to make this expansion worth it for me.
<br />

<br />
Yes, WoS is packed to the gills during peak time. Humble suggestion, go somewhere else. OoW offers a LOT of nice zones. NC, Bloodfields, MPG, Riftseekers if yer high enough(I'm not), RCoD... and randomly, RARELY but randomly you get elemental level drops off total trash mobs. 
<br />

<br />
Yes We have to go through a lotta shitty spells before we get to the really sweet ones. Would you rather be competing with all the other casters for parchments then getting the same shitty spells over and over and over and over before you get to the good spells? Or maybe have the spells drop from mobs no reasonable pre-elemental group is gonna be able to GET to let alone kill? Any 65 mage with any sort of people skills whatsoever can get these. Yeah they're camped to hell now. The expansion just came out, what were you expecting? You can get em in expeditions. Yes they made them harder to farm, not impossible but harder. However it's a chance. At the start of PoP did you have a chance at getting spec parchment drops from one groupable named mobs within the first couple weeks of release? If you were in tier two or three, yeah. The casual gamer wasn't.
<br />

<br />
To sum up folks, this is one of the best expansions we've seen to date. Unlike GoD or even luclin, you have a shot at taking a group of pre-elemental 65s and getting elemental level upgrades and spells. OoW ain't perfect, but it's the best we've seen in years. And having a pet within the first week of release that can outtank a plate class... Well that's just plain nice.
<br />

<br />
- Faelawen Starfyre, the Mad Mage of Povar</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
